issue.title: ArgumentError in Admin wrong number of arguments (1 for 0)

repository.name: activeadmin
repository.description: The administration framework for Ruby on Rails applications.

issue.body:
Having this error on only one model. This model belongs_to another one, but I have a few has many models on that are working well.  

Extracted source (around line #48):

``` ruby
          temp_method = "__temp__#{safe_name}"
          ActiveRecord::AttributeMethods::AttrNames.set_name_cache safe_name, name
          @module.module_eval method_body(temp_method, safe_name), __FILE__, __LINE__
          @module.instance_method temp_method
        end
      end
```

Using the latest version or activeadmin:

```
gem 'activeadmin', '~> 1.0.0.pre2'
gem 'sass-rails', '~> 5.0'
```

and wasn't able to install meta_search because of a looping issue.
